<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="7" pageNumber="222" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1974,2035]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="223" pageId="7" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1974,1999]" pageId="7" pageNumber="222">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: White pubescence covering entire body, denser on head, most of mesosoma and ovipositor sheath, sparser on metapleuron and most of metasoma. Head turquoise green, with antenna dark brown, mandible yellow with well developed, dark brown teeth (
<figureCitation box="[609,679,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,939,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1437,939,1934]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. 9–10 Lepidura patagonica new species: 9 Head (frontal view); 10 Habitus. 11–12: L. seminitida new species: 11 Head (frontal view); 12 Habitus. Scale bars (mm): Figs. 9 and 11 = 0.4; Figs. 10 and 12 = 2.0." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607955/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Body turquoise green, except mesoscutum, mesothorax, anterior and posterior margins of T2, anterior margin of T3 and T6–9, dark brown. Posterior margins of T3–5 light brown. Legs turquoise green; anterior margin of femur, anterior and posterior margins of all tibiae and tarsi brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,939,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1437,939,1934]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. 9–10 Lepidura patagonica new species: 9 Head (frontal view); 10 Habitus. 11–12: L. seminitida new species: 11 Head (frontal view); 12 Habitus. Scale bars (mm): Figs. 9 and 11 = 0.4; Figs. 10 and 12 = 2.0." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607955/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="223" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,548,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">
<typeStatus box="[352,461,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Holotype</typeStatus>
female
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[565,690,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1960,1983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,939,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1437,939,1934]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. 9–10 Lepidura patagonica new species: 9 Head (frontal view); 10 Habitus. 11–12: L. seminitida new species: 11 Head (frontal view); 12 Habitus. Scale bars (mm): Figs. 9 and 11 = 0.4; Figs. 10 and 12 = 2.0." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607955/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Figs. 9, 10</figureCitation>
). Approximate body length: 11.0 mm. Fore wing length: 
<quantity box="[1342,1432,296,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="7.3">7.3 mm</quantity>
; antenna length: 
<quantity box="[340,434,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
; number of flagellomeres: 40–42; head 1.15× as wide as high (front view); distance between eye and lateral ocellus 1.00× as long as diameter of lateral ocellus; frons smooth,; clypeus 0.50× as wide as high; mandible 3.10× as long as basal width (front view); mandible with two well developed teeth; mandible basal width 1.90× as long as malar space; pronotum polished; hind femur 11.05× as long as wide; hind tibia 9.25× as long as wide; hind basitarsus 14.10× as long as wide; mesosoma generally smooth, polished and finely punctate; areolet large, rhombic, 1.50× as wide as long; hind wing with 5 hamuli; propodeum smooth, with isolated punctures; areola absent, but with subpentagonal area delimited by complete lateral longitudinal and posterior transverse carina and incomplete anterior transverse and median longitudinal carina (
<figureCitation box="[1116,1182,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1305,1328]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,796,1282]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1437,796,1282]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Propodeum in dorsal view. 1–2 Propodeum without areola: 1 Propodeum with subpentagonal area delimited by complete lateral longitudinal and posterior transverse carinae and incomplete anterior transverse and median longitudinal carinae, Lepidura abbreviata Dash, 1974; 2 Propodeum smooth, with reduced carinae, L. olivacea Dash, 1974; 3 Propodeum with areola delimited by the median longitudinal, anterior transverse and posterior transverse carinae, L. improcera Dash, 1974. Scale bars (mm): Figs 1–3 = 0.2." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2607944/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); postpetiole 1.80× as long as maximum width; glymma deep, seemingly with thin membrane between both sides; T1–T7 smooth, with isolated punctures; T2 4.85× as long as its height (lateral view); hypopygium large and triangular in lateral view ventral extremity weakly scletorized, 2.00× as long as wide; ovipositor sheath, 1.50× as long as basal width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,392,727,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,727,752]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Male</emphasis>
