<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="223" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" box="[199,983,908,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,908,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Etymology</emphasis>
: The species is named after the region of the 
<typeStatus box="[838,886,909,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,151,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,342,943,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Comentário</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Araujo &amp; Vivallo, 2018" authorityName="Araujo &amp; Vivallo" authorityYear="2018" box="[358,595,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lepidura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[358,595,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">Lepidura patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,695,943,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[604,695,943,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="223" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dasch" authorityYear="1974" box="[847,950,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lepidura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[847,862,945,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[878,950,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of vein CU/1b on the hind wing and the lentgh of the T2, 2.50× its width or longer. The two species can be differentiated by the presence of the costula and the anterior transverse carina of propodeum, absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dasch" authorityYear="1974" box="[954,1057,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Lepidura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[954,1057,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="223">L. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. There was no variation between the specimens, this is the larger species in the genus.
</paragraph>
